analysis.Summary: Vue single-file component that renders an SVG icon representing a "finished status". It exposes a single prop `fill` to control the icon color.
analysis.Purpose: Provide a reusable status icon (finished state) throughout the application wherever a "finished" indicator is needed.

Components.name: IconStatusFinished
responsibilities: Render an SVG with a predefined path that visually represents a completed/finished status.
Accept a `fill` prop to customize the icon's fill color.

Functions.name: defineProps
Functions.purpose: Declare component props using the Composition API.

fill.description: SVG path fill color, defaults to CSS variable for black.

analysis.Usage:
Imported in other Vue components or pages via:
```js
import IconStatusFinished from 'modules/orders/components/icons/IconStatusFinished.vue'
```
Then used in a template:
```html
<IconStatusFinished fill="#34A853" />
```
Notes: No `<style>` section â€“ styling is controlled via SVG attributes and CSS variables.
Purely presentational; contains no emitted events or reactive state beyond props.
Fits into an icon library or design system under the orders module.
